While investigating why build times are increasing I found it very difficult to manually calculate how long each step took by timestamp.

 

I would be nice to have something like this in the logs:
{noformat}
simple 08-Nov-2016 15:42:48 Finished task 'npm run build' with result: Success, after 4.2 min
{noformat}

h3. Problem Definition

When downloading the YAML configuration, we are looking for Top-Level plans only, so this fails when the export is triggered from a Plan Branch
{code:java}
final ImmutableTopLevelPlan immutableTopLevelPlan
                = cachedPlanManager.getPlanByKey(getImmutablePlan().getPlanKey(), ImmutableTopLevelPlan.class);

{code}
h3. Suggested Solution
 * Truncate {{PROJ-PLAN[BRANCH]}} to {{PROJ-PLAN}}
 * Allow Plan Branch to trigger YAML export

h3. Workaround

Navigate to the Master or main branch of your Plan before triggering the YAML export
